race.description: New Years Eve Family Race Day 31 Dec Handicap
race.comment: EMBALLEE (6) finally put it all together at start seven when recording a comprehensive maiden win over 1600m at Hawkesbury. Looks to have more upside than most of these and maps to get the right run. INVASIVE DREAMS (4) back sharply in class after going out hard for a tiring fifth over 1600m at Randwick in the Filante. Will relish Grima's 3kg claim and shapes as a genuine top-three prospect. DRUNKEN SAILOR (9) has started to hit his straps at his last two runs. Impressed when picking them up effortlessly for a decisive win over 1460m at Queanbeyan in C3 class. Looks up to this at the good each-way price. WHETU (1) in need of the run first-up over the unsuitable trip when last of ten over 1350m at Newcastle. This looks more to his liking and can surprise some of his more fancied rivals.
